      "Safe boarding plan submitted and approved by New Orleans District"
    ],
    "summary": "On 17 October 2020 at 0445 hours, an oil tanker ship drifted into the northwest leg of the SP 57-B platform causing approximately $1.5 million in damage to the platform's leg, boat landing, sump deck, and stairs. Five production operators were onboard and safely evacuated with no injuries. The allision was caused by the vessel anchoring too close to the platform and subsequently drifting during anchor retrieval. No pollution or gas leaks resulted from the incident. The platform's safety systems functioned properly.",
